records.englishText:
Hadith.5316 - It was narrated by Muhammad ibn Ismaʿil ibn Buzayʿ from Ṣalih ibn Uqbah from Sulayman ibn Ṣalih from Abu Abdullah (as) who said:
"Indeed, for the sperm-drop (nutfah) there is a compensation of twenty dinars,
for the clot (Alaqah) forty dinars,
for the lump of flesh (muḍghah) sixty dinars,
for the bone (Aẓm) eighty dinars,
and when it is clothed with flesh, it is one hundred dinars.
Then it remains one hundred until it lets out a cry (at birth), and when it lets out a cry, the full blood money (diyyah) becomes due."

